article.description: — Derek St. Hilaire made four 3-pointers and finished with 20 points as No. 5 seed New Orleans beat eighth-seeded Southeastern Louisiana 80-63 in the second round of the Southland Conference tournament on Wednesday night.
article.headline: New Orleans beats SE Louisiana 80-63 in Southland tourney
article.linkText: New Orleans beats SE Louisiana 80-63 in Southland tourney
article.story: KATY, Texas -- — Derek St. Hilaire made four 3-pointers and finished with 20 points as No. 5 seed New Orleans beat eighth-seeded Southeastern Louisiana 80-63 in the second round of the Southland Conference tournament on Wednesday night. The Privateers will play No. 4 seed Northwestern State in a quarterfinal on Thursday. Damion Rosser added 15 points for New Orleans (10-14). Troy Green had 11 points and Rodney Carson Jr. and Ahren Freeman 10 apiece. Keon Clergeot had 22 points and Isiah Kirby added 10 for the Lions (8-18). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
